
# Complete Summary: Exponential vs Pareto Distributions

## 1. EXPONENTIAL DISTRIBUTION - Constant Additive Decay

### How the tail decays:
**CCDF(x) = e^(-Î»x)**

**Key property: CONSTANT % loss per UNIT STEP**

Example with Î» = 1:
```
x  | P(X > x) | % lost from previous
---|----------|---------------------
0  | 1.000    | -
1  | 0.368    | 63.2%
2  | 0.135    | 63.2% â† SAME!
3  | 0.050    | 63.2% â† SAME!
10 | 0.000045 | 63.2% â† ALWAYS SAME!
```

**Every single step (+1), you lose the same percentage!**

### Result:
- âœ… **Finite mean** (always)
- âœ… **Finite variance** (always)
- âœ… **All moments finite**
- ðŸ“Š **Light tail** - extreme events very rare

