## 2. PARETO DISTRIBUTION - Constant Multiplicative Decay

### How the tail decays:
**CCDF(x) = x^(-Î±)**

**Key property: CONSTANT % loss per MULTIPLICATIVE JUMP (Ã—k)**

**Ã—10 jump keeps: 10^(-Î±)**
**Ã—10 jump loses: 1 - 10^(-Î±)**

### Examples with different Î±:

#### Î± = 1:
```
x    | P(X > x) | % kept per Ã—10 jump
-----|----------|--------------------
1    | 1.000    | -
10   | 0.100    | 10% âœ“
100  | 0.010    | 10% âœ“
1000 | 0.001    | 10% âœ“
```
**Loses 90% per Ã—10 jump (constant!)**

#### Î± = 1.5:
```
