-----|----------|--------------------
1    | 1.000    | -
10   | 0.0316   | 3.16% âœ“
100  | 0.001    | 3.16% âœ“
1000 | 0.0000316| 3.16% âœ“
```
**Loses 96.84% per Ã—10 jump (constant!)**

#### Î± = 2:
```
x    | P(X > x) | % kept per Ã—10 jump
-----|----------|--------------------
1    | 1.000    | -
10   | 0.010    | 1% âœ“
100  | 0.0001   | 1% âœ“
1000 | 0.000001 | 1% âœ“
```
**Loses 99% per Ã—10 jump (constant!)**

### BUT: Unit steps show DECREASING % loss!

For Î± = 1:
```
x  | P(X > x) | % lost from previous UNIT step
---|----------|--------------------------------
1  | 1.000    | -
2  | 0.500    | 50%
3  | 0.333    | 33% â† getting smaller!
4  | 0.250    | 25% â† still shrinking!
10 | 0.100    | 11%
100| 0.010    | 2%  â† very small now!
```

**This is what makes it "heavy-tailed" - it holds on longer than exponential!**

