## 6. KEY FORMULAS SUMMARY

### Exponential:
- **CCDF:** e^(-Î»x)
- **% kept per +1 step:** e^(-Î») = **constant**
- **Mean:** Always finite = 1/Î»
- **Variance:** Always finite = 1/Î»Â²

### Pareto:
- **CCDF:** x^(-Î±)
- **% kept per Ã—k jump:** k^(-Î±) = **constant**
- **% kept per Ã—10 jump:** 10^(-Î±)
- **Mean band ratio:** 10^(1-Î±)
  - Finite if Î± > 1
- **Variance band ratio:** 10^(2-Î±)
  - Finite if Î± > 2
- **k-th moment band ratio:** 10^(k-Î±)
  - Finite if Î± > k

---

## 7. THE BIG PICTURE

**Exponential = "Giving up quickly"**
- Constant % decay per unit step
- Extreme values become unlikely VERY fast
- All moments exist
- Like radioactive decay

**Pareto = "Persistent tail"**
- Constant % decay per Ã—10 jump, but SLOWING decay per unit step
- Extreme values stay relatively likely
- Moments may not exist (depends on Î±)
- Like wealth distribution, city sizes, earthquake magnitudes

**The Critical Boundaries:**
- **Î± = 1:** Mean switches from infinite to finite
- **Î± = 2:** Variance switches from infinite to finite
- **Î± = k:** k-th moment switches from infinite to finite

**Why Ã—10 jump constant % doesn't mean exponential:**
- Exponential: constant % per ADDITIVE step (+1, +1, +1...)
- Pareto: constant % per MULTIPLICATIVE step (Ã—10, Ã—10, Ã—10...)
- Very different behaviors!
